Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.00,0:00:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,well we're here because we're here because we're here\Nwhat a wonderful uh crowd and you've been meditating this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.15,0:00:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful i always say glory to god glory and excelsis deo if that makes you nervous\Nthis is the wrong place to be today
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.67,0:01:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,such things become rote if you're a religionist and you forget the power that you invoke into\Nyour life the 91st psalm which is uh one of my favorites says those who call upon me are mine
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.94,0:01:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,krishna says those who call upon me are mine so those who call upon god live under the protection\Nof the almighty
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.41,0:01:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,hey that's a comforting thought in today's world\Nthe lady who jumped uh at 13 000 feet and the parachute didn't open
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.53,0:01:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,i was wondering what she was thinking about on the way down\Nguess i should have gone to church or something
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.78,0:02:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,uh yes\Nwell today we're going to talk about really uh advancing one's level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.42,0:02:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in today's today's world uh frankly due to the work that's been done the chances of reaching\Nenlightenment are now a thousand times greater than at any time in history a thousand times
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.34,0:02:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,greater\Nlet's see if that's true what i just stated is true or resist okay those of you who are
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.82,0:02:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar with the work know that uh we use a lot of words that are not the same as the\Nwords of the church we use a lot of words that are not the same as the church because
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.82,0:02:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology as a means, as a measuring tool. I've got a, what do you want to call it, a finger,\Nfinger, you know, and it's interesting to meet here. This property, I used to spend a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.03,0:03:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,time, oh, 35 years ago. It was the site of a monastic group, Zen Catholicism, a synthesis of\NZen and Catholicism, and the monks all lived in separate little huts, and there was a meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.11,0:03:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,center, and I used to come to the meditation center in the dark at 4 30 or 5 in the morning,\Nand you had the meditation center all to yourself, a kiva, a meditation kiva,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.40,0:03:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had it all. It was just a big circular building with a nice carpet, and I could meditate\Nfor hours absolutely alone. It was wonderful. Zen Catholicism. They later moved on to Colorado
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.36,0:03:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because Sedona became too crowded. At the time I came here, the population was a little less than\N3,000. It's now like 18,000, so when they got 3,000, they got up to four or five. They thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.09,0:04:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was getting crowded here, and they left. It seems comical, huh? All right, so today I thought\Na number of you are familiar with the work I've done, and so I'm going to recapitulate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.62,0:04:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you how it all originated, you know. I had a huge psychiatric practice, and\Nit was the largest in the United States, frankly, and we had a couple of thousand outpatients,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.46,0:04:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had a huge staff, and we treated the most hopeless patients from all over the world.\NThey flew them in from every country, and some had very rich parents. They were Maharaj in India,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.64,0:04:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, multi, huge amount of money, and so these patients had been everywhere,\Nseeing everybody. They'd seen every professor, and they're all hopeless, the most hopeless of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.46,0:05:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,all cases. So those were the patients that I specialized, the most hopeless of all, and we used\Nalternate therapies. Medical science itself calibrates as a science about 440, but clinical
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.01,0:05:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,science, that's academic science, calibrates around 440. Clinical science calibrates five\Npoints higher, 445. So it takes into account the effect of the healer, the presence of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.61,0:05:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,physician, and the consciousness level of the physician, too, you see. So I had a huge staff,\Nof psychiatrists, and I noticed that some had very high rates of recovery, and others didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.29,0:05:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As it turned out later, those with the higher levels of consciousness had the highest rating\Nof healings, because they brought the power of intention, and the power of intention. We'll get
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.35,0:06:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,around to quantum mechanics later, but the Heisenberg principle, you understand, precipitates\Npotentiality becoming an actuality. And what hasn't been measured is the power of the effect of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.83,0:06:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer. It's taken as an abstract concept in the work of Henry Stapp at Berkeley, explains the\Nscientific basis of it. But what we haven't measured yet is there's a difference between the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of the observer. So a person with a weak level of consciousness,\Ndoesn't experience miracles, doesn't even see miracles. And to other people, the miraculous is a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.02,0:07:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous reality. The fact that I'm alive and breathing today is already a miracle.\NWell, I didn't want to listen to him talk all morning. So I was gonna tell you how this all started.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.15,0:07:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes. So, we had a Course in Miracles group, so we knew that there was a certain thing that was going to be\Nin my life at the end of the day. And I don't know about you, but I knew that I would have to go to my
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,best friends and friends, and I knew that I was going to have to go to my best friends, and my best friend was going to have to go to my best friend. And I knew that he had\Ngroup there. It was the second, whatchamacallit, healing center in the United States. The first
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,one was in Tiburon, and Jerry came out with his whole staff and spoke to our staff. So\Nwe had the second attitudinal healing center in the United States based on the Course in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.49,0:07:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles. That was for hopeless patients at the clinic. And so we had patients with every\Nkind of disease known to mankind who practiced the Course in Miracles. So I had studied something
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,about kinesiology. I'd heard that that's a new way you could diagnose and help treat\Npatients. And so I went and learned about it, and I came back to lecture to the staff
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.27,0:08:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about what I had learned. And I found that there were certain people, oh, I know what\NI did. I said, I need some volunteers for the kinesiology demonstration tonight. And
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.26,0:08:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a few of them were hanging out because they were meeting with the attitudinal healing\Ncenter. And I said, come on over here, let me see, and we'll test you tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I tested them with fluorescent lights or pesticides, things that make everybody\Ngo weak, these people did not go weak. In teaching kinesiology, I used to just, you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.01,0:08:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,pass out synthetic sugar substitutes or pesticides or look at fluorescent lights, everybody goes\Nweak looking at fluorescent lights. But these people did not. They looked at the fluorescent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.74,0:08:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,light and their arms stayed strong.\NI said, what's the matter with this guy? Then I tried pesticides. That didn't make
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:09:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,them go weak either. So something was different about this group that was doing the Course\Nin Miracles from ordinary people. So a new group was starting doing the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tested them periodically. I tested them about once a week. And of course, they went\Nweak to fluorescent lights. These fluorescent lights would make everybody go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.31,0:09:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I found around less than 90 or so, after they'd been in the Course about three\Nmonths, suddenly negative stimuli did not make them go weak anymore. I said, wow-zee,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that's fantastic.\NAnd from that, we then devised a measuring system of one to a thousand. And kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.52,0:09:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is not understood by people at all. They think it has to do with, they don't understand that\Nit's objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.04,0:10:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, in the presence of truth, physiologically, you go strong via your acupuncture\Nsystem. And there's other physiologic phenomena, such as the pupillary response. So some people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.55,0:10:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,like to ridicule kinesiology. It's because they don't understand it. Because people who\Nare stuck in the linear pedestrian domain of intellectual development don't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.75,0:10:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-linear.\NTherefore, the skeptics...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.07,0:10:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,are stuck with the fact that they have a very pedestrian mentality. Below 200, you\Ndon't understand the non-linear domain. Because reality emerges as a consequence, not only
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.13,0:10:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of content, but of context. And the skeptic is unaware of the power of the field, the\Nnon-linear field of context. Consequently, a physician who believes in God has a higher
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.48,0:10:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,cure rate. They want to know what the cure rate is. They want to know what the cure rate\Nis. They want to know what the cure rate is. They want to know what the cure rate is. They
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.42,0:11:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,want to know what the cure rate is. They want to know what the cure rate is. They've\Nsteel-resistant the lecture every lesson from 10 to 18 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.52,0:11:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But they don't discover it. They don't have a full view of time. What needed, at home,\Nis to see the perfect state.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue mean proposed.\NRed mean prescribed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.62,0:11:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We have Amtrak...\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.34,0:11:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\Nhas never been known becomes instantly knowable why is that because in the infinite reality
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.02,0:11:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness in the beginning was the light in the beginning was the godhead\Nout of the godhead emerged divinity as the creator from which reated forth the light of god
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.48,0:12:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of god is the field of consciousness itself which is infinite infinite all present\Nwith no beginning and no end so the ultimate context of our work is the field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.68,0:12:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,itself which is the presence of divinity in the non-linear domain in other words an infinitely\Npowerful field and by virtue of that field all things manifest out of potentiality so
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.16,0:12:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to see as your consciousness advances\Nyou begin to see as your consciousness advances
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.82,0:12:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to see as your consciousness advances\Nthat there is no such thing as causality in the world causality is a linear newtonian concept of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.08,0:12:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this causing of that which calibrates in the 400s actually the way things happen is potentiality\Nactualize actualizes under appropriate conditions potentiality becomes actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.24,0:13:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,not out of causality but out of the emergence the potentiality even\Nan thats
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.06,0:13:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,emerges as an actuality the flower is not there's no flower by virtue of force nobody forces\Nthe flower to come forth but within the flower is that potentiality and the local conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.83,0:13:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are appropriate.\NIt shines forth with the radiance of its existence that's how all things come into existence
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.42,0:13:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,its potentiality actualize and our best definition of\Nit in the linear domain or in the comprehensible domain, is the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Stapp, S-T-E-P-P, out of Berkeley on the Internet, has probably the best delineation\Nof the application of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:14:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality actualizes when conditions are appropriate.\NOne of the conditions, then, is your own state of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.21,0:14:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you hold in mind then tends to actualize.\NWhat you hold in mind tends to actualize, yes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact, resist.\NWhat you hold in mind tends to actualize, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.26,0:14:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Not based on causality, so you can't cause yourself to become rich, or cause yourself\Nto become famous, or cause yourself, and you see everybody out in the world trying to cause
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.34,0:14:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves to be successful, and .\NIt's entertaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.44,0:14:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway, the way to success is to be completely and totally the fulfillment of your own potential\Nto the best degree that you can fulfill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.89,0:15:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,To be the best carpenter in town, to be the best shoemaker in town, to perfect whatever\Ncapacities you have, to be the best mother there is, the best father, to be an upright
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.99,0:15:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and responsible citizen.\NTo be, to have good will towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.77,0:15:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To contextualize your life, all you need to do, you don't have to sit and meditate, you\Ndon't have to go um and om, you don't have to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.68,0:15:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is have good will towards all of life and all of its expressions, no\Nmatter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.92,0:15:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just give you the example, in previous lifetimes being beheaded.\NSo you say to the headsman, listen, don't feel nervous, it's okay, it's only your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.91,0:15:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not your job.\NThat's what I always tell them, don't worry about it, it's only your job, and you're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.99,0:15:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a good job of it, thank you, thank you.\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.00,0:15:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So your last thought is good will towards the headsman, that he doesn't feel guilty\Nabout this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.76,0:16:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It is that he's fulfilling his obligation to the crown, he's fulfilling his obligation\Nto the crown, and therefore he's worthy of respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.51,0:16:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I respect the head, I always respect the headsman.\NWhen it's another one of those heads-off lifetimes, which I haven't had in quite a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.26,0:16:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, well let's start with the, we'll start with how we usually do this.\NThe map of consciousness then evolved, Lager-Nik, these are all numbers to the 10th power.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.46,0:16:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is 10 to the 600th power.\NThis is 10 times the 20th power, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.00,0:16:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the power, it goes up.\NIt goes up very, very rapidly as you get into higher numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As you get into higher numbers.\NTherefore a loving thought is, I forget how many times, 10 million or some odd number,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.96,0:17:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,more powerful than a negative thought.\NSo stop feeling guilty about your negative thoughts, because they're weak and feeble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.72,0:17:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,One loving thought will undo all the negative thoughts you've had all day.\NThat's a fact, oh Lord, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.94,0:17:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NI never asked that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.94,0:17:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But.\NI just know it experientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One loving thought is transformative.\NIt undoes all the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.36,0:17:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause you see, here you're hitting somebody, the power of that is 20, 20 times 10, 10 times
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,10, 20 times, 10 times 10, 20 times.\NA loving thought is 10 times 10, 500 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.57,0:17:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how enormously powerful.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.92,0:17:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A loving thought is.\NSo to be, people say, how do you reach enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.78,0:18:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, be loving towards all of life and all of its expressions at all times.\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.27,0:18:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodwill and lovingness towards all of life.\NSo that lovingness, it isn't love, it's lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.83,0:18:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,See, love here is at 500.\NLovingness is maybe at about 540 on up to 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.74,0:18:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is the 12 step groups.\NAlcoholics Anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.62,0:18:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Unselfish lovingness and goodwill towards others.\NSo as you advance spiritually, that which you hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.69,0:18:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And you also discover if you have any negative thoughts, too, as you hear something falling\Noff the wall, you say, well, God, I didn't really mean to think that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.49,0:18:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.24,0:18:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens then is what people are critical about kinesiology and they can't get off their\Nown narcissistic orientation towards life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.98,0:19:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They presume that everything we say or every calibration is a personal opinion.\NThey don't get appearance from essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.90,0:19:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's appearance and then there's essence, as Descartes pointed out.\NAnd the difficulty, as Socrates says, is man cannot differentiate appearance from essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.60,0:19:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence is the innate essence.\NThe essence is the innate essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.60,0:19:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence is the innate truth.\NThat which is how it is in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.42,0:19:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Appearance is what you think about it.\NI'm not interested in what anybody thinks about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.90,0:19:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not interested in anybody's opinion about anything because opinions are worthless.\NYou can go on the Internet and there's millions and millions of and you calibrate them, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.91,0:19:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,all under 200.\NWell, 200 is a magic number.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.32,0:19:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We found that anything below 200 makes you go weak and anything over 200 makes you go\Nstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.49,0:20:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time, the first time in all of human history, there was a way of discerning\Ntruth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.02,0:20:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know that in one second, we can discern the truth or the falsehood of anything, anywhere\Nin time, anywhere in the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen percent of the audience got what I said, 85 percent do not.\NBy the end of the day, we hope we'll increase this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.36,0:20:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this?\NBecause in the infinite dimensionless field of the universe, there's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing.\NThere's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.26,0:20:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no center.\NNothing is present, there is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.55,0:20:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing in the infinite realm.\NEverything is a field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.55,0:20:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no center.\NThere is no center to an infinite universe, neither is there a past or a present or a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.81,0:20:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,future.\NTherefore, everything is happening now, yours is discernable now, and everywhere is right
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,here.\NWhat Napoleon thought about and how he felt before he walked into the Pyramid and how
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.46,0:21:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he felt after he walked out of the Pyramid is knowable right this instant.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.03,0:21:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because outside of time, there is no then, now, or future.\NYou cannot use kinesiology to determine the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.41,0:21:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?\NBecause the future is not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.35,0:21:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a hypothetical potentiality.\NSo the future isn't set.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, books telling you about the prophecies of the future all calibrate negative.\NAll of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.95,0:21:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single one of them calibrates true.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because potentiality is actualizing based on an infinite field.\NAnd part of the infinite field is your decision from moment to moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.56,0:21:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The future hasn't happened yet because we haven't created it yet.\NBecause what we're holding in mind is what's creating the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.45,0:21:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you predict that which has no reality?\NIt has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.86,0:22:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you cannot predict the future.\NYou don't have to understand me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.47,0:22:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.37,0:22:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact.\NYou can't predict the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.21,0:22:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why in the New Testament, the book of Revelations, calibrates it 70.\NI treated a lot of people with apocalyptic triumphalism delusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.93,0:22:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a realm in the lower astral, calibrates it 70.\NPeople periodically go over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.49,0:22:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There was somebody here in Sedona, very well known, who had quite a few fathers.\NAnd he had gone over there and was predicting end times, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.91,0:23:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at that calibrated level of 70, there's an astral realm where the apocalyptic catastrophic is a continuous ongoing play.\NAnd if you go out of body, your spirit goes over there, you experience it as a reality, you come back here and tell everybody that the end is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.11,0:23:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And every generation, there's people walking up and down the sidewalks, repent, the end is coming.\NThe future isn't here because we haven't created it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.36,0:23:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In human experience, the collective consciousness of mankind, which was at 190,\Nthe collective consciousness of mankind calibrated at 90 at the time of the birth of the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.82,0:23:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrated about 100 at the time of the birth of Jesus Christ.\NIt slowly rose over the centuries and got as far as about 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.20,0:23:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And there it stayed for many centuries.\NIt stayed right at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.66,0:23:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And up until the late 1980s.\NIt was at 190 and then suddenly in the late 1980s, it jumped to 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.34,0:24:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It then, a couple of years later, that we were lecturing in San Francisco when it did it, it went from 205 to 207 at the time of the Harmonic Concordance.\NAnd since that time, it has gone back down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.57,0:24:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what it is this morning.\NYou have to take the world's temperature every day, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.39,0:24:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThe collective consciousness of mankind, we have permission to ask that or resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.79,0:24:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's currently over 204.\NCurrently over 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.38,0:24:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,204.\NSo it was up to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.68,0:24:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It went down to 204.\NI was a little disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was going to keep evolving in a steady course, but it didn't.\NSo, for reasons, I don't know myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.58,0:24:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't worry about it.\NI don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.16,0:24:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness of...\NI don't know if there's any tax points on it for now, but I hope I do with the states,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.32,0:25:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and history has, you know, the basic idea of the us has a certain Norman.\NSo, that thing you have been questioning it lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.23,0:25:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My pleasure.\NI was so told so many things that it was almost like a golden age.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.09,0:25:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the kind of lights that keepOnly a boost out of the earth.\NSo of course, we'd get stuck on rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.57,0:25:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been about five years, I guess.\NAnd historically...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.64,0:25:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And historically, we have looked.\NA lot, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.96,0:25:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, wow.\Nis that? Singapore is over 430, 435. Singapore is ahead of us. I think they're so good. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.32,0:25:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where do they see our new iPod-y-doodle? iPod-y-doodle, where do they see our new iPod-y-doodle?\NThat'll show them Singaporeans. Level of consciousness, then, is correlated with your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.12,0:26:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of divinity, your view of yourself. The level of consciousness here, we've depicted\Nit all the way from enlightenment down to suicidal shame, the logarithm, the emotion that goes with
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.90,0:26:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it, and the process going on in consciousness itself. And as you'll notice, these are all very\Ndestructive down here. Then you become a good deal freer. You begin to transcend, transfigure,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.59,0:26:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,illumination, and reach the states of enlightenment, which are really from 600 and up.\NI say the 12-step groups are at about 540. Sainthood is at about 570. Mother Therese,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.20,0:26:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sainthood, who's, let's see, who's the 570? Father Pio, various people,\NSainthood, the last Pope was 570. This Pope is 565, which is practically the same range. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.71,0:27:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have respect for the Pope, and you don't have to be a Catholic to respect the fact that his\Ncommitment is to Christianity as he understands it. Okay. And the Dalai Lama, various people,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.00,0:27:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,uh-huh. And anyway, that's neither here nor there. We'll go on to the next thing. Where's the next,\Nwhat'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.58,0:27:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NWhere's the next slide? Oh. This is the world's population, the distribution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.42,0:27:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the world. And you see, here's the level of truth to integrity at 200. Everything\Nbelow here is false. Everything below 200 is false and destructive. You see that approximately 80
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.13,0:28:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,percent of the world's population lives in the destructive realm of consciousness. There are\Ncountries where 100 percent of the people are below 200. Therefore, our diplomatic attempts at
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.93,0:28:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,conciliation with serenity, peace, honesty, and truth do not go too far in certain places in the\Nworld because this truth sounds to these people like falsehood. So, there's a flip side. We'll
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.27,0:28:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,show in a kind of slide later. This flip side has to do with, actually, with brain physiology. From\N200, consciousness level 200, which is commitment to truth and integrity for its own sake, not for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.86,0:28:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,personal gain, uh, people process with a different side of the brain. So, these people here process\Nprimarily with the animal side of the brain. And once the kundalini energy begins to rise, the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.94,0:28:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 200, the kundalini energy begins to rise. Once it does, it shifts your brain\Nprocessing to right brain, and you see and experience things differently. So, you see and experience things
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.46,0:29:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,differently because the brain physiology processes things differently. And we have a slide on that\Nlater. Therefore, how approximation is going to be brought between civilizations, one processes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.31,0:29:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,things with the animal instinct side of the brain, and this one processes things with the kundalini\Nenergy side of the brain. And how you're going to get an approximation, I have no idea. That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.26,0:29:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we need God. God, we need God.\NYou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.08,0:29:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, you already got help. I said, oh, yes, you got help, cause you gotta solve this conundrum of\Nhow, what you're gonna do about all this. So, the purpose to my life of, to my way of seeing of human
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.43,0:30:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,life is that this world is perfect the way it is. I'm not interested in improving the world. Why?\NBecause the world as it is, is absolutely perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.92,0:30:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's designed to be perfect.\Nis for the advancement of human consciousness and if that is the purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.46,0:30:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of human life, the advancement of consciousness, then this is the perfect\Nworld. What's the karmic merit if you don't have anybody to hate, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.74,0:30:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying? Who's there to forgive? All right, so anyway, we'll move on to the next.\NSo this is the distribution of consciousness levels of mankind and you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.69,0:30:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,see people from 200 and up, which characterizes an audience like this, and\Nthe naivety of these people is they project this onto the world and think
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.67,0:31:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,these people are like you. They are not like you. You feel constrained to tell\Nthe truth. In their mind, to tell the truth is idiotic and stupid, can probably
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.56,0:31:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,get you killed if not fired or executed, because your duty is to do what brings\Ngain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.32,0:31:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Period. Not truth. Telling the truth will get you executed in a good part of\Nthis living world today. Uh-huh. Contrary. So you've got a 180. So in understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.77,0:31:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the world then, you have to understand that many people think completely the\Nopposite from which you do. Uh-huh. We consider benevolence a virtue. Half the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.11,0:31:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,world considers benevolence a despicable weakness.\NWeakness. Okay. So this helps us understand how to deal with the world and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.33,0:32:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,especially international diplomacy. All right, we'll move to the next one. Uh-huh.\NHow people see. You see, as a psychiatrist and psychoanalyst, when a patient comes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.96,0:32:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in, it's not his responsibility to understand where I am. It's my\Nresponsibility to understand where he is. And we're walking around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.53,0:32:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,saying, you should understand where we are. No, we should understand where they are.\Nso we know how to communicate with them, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.03,0:32:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we think is a lovely idea,\Nthey think is ridiculous, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.00,0:32:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is just the way the whole thing balances out.\NWhat you see is that although there's very few people
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.74,0:32:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at the top of the pyramid,\Ntheir power is so enormous that they counterbalance
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.04,0:32:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity of the rest of the population.\NWhat you need is a few people, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.10,0:32:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in a very high level of consciousness\Nto counterbalance all the negativity of an entire country.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.48,0:32:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's move on to the next.\NCalibration level 1,000, for instance, of the great avatar,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.41,0:32:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,1,000 will counterbalance all the negativity\Nof all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.20,0:33:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need is one enlightened teacher on the planet\Nto counterbalance the total negativity of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.58,0:33:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a logarithmic progression,\Nand 10 times 10 times 10,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.90,0:33:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand times is a significant amount of power.\NSo we'll move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.60,0:33:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NLet's move back to the last one, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.20,0:33:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is evolution of consciousness over elapsed time.\NAnd you see it was practically at a standstill
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.86,0:33:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for millions of years, and this is the way it's moving now.\NSo this is why I thought, well, consciousness is going to go up,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.02,0:33:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and lately it's been going down a few points,\Nwhich we'll have to change the graph and put a squiggle in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.34,0:33:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Squiggle.\NOkay, well, move to the next one, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.74,0:34:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so this is the evolution of consciousness.\NYou see, to understand the evolution of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.44,0:34:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand out of the radiance of divinity,\Nout of the light of divinity shown forth,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.80,0:34:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,its interaction with matter and organic matter spawned life.\NSo life emerged.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.22,0:34:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NLife emerged as a consequence of the presence of the infinite power of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.04,0:34:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in its interaction with material world.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.84,0:34:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The light of divinity, when it's shown upon matter,\Nout of that arose organicity, and out of that arose life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.27,0:34:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The most primitive forms of life, of course, animal life, protoplasmic life,\Ndoes not have within itself a source of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.64,0:34:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,not a source of energy.\NNot a single rabbit, not a single protozoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.59,0:34:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They all have to get energy.\NYou see, vegetative life has chlorophyll,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.75,0:35:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you're a plant, all you've got to do is sit there.\NThe sun shines on you, and you get all the energy you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.72,0:35:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to acquire or get.\NIf you're protoplasmic, however, you won't live very long unless you get energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.89,0:35:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no source of energy.\NYou have to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.51,0:35:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,To get energy, you have to sample what's out there.\NIf you're a little amoeba, you have to try this, you have to try that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.15,0:35:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a little sip of this, and then .\NOver the millennia, life then learned that which is favorable to life and that which is unfavorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.14,0:35:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you didn't learn that, you didn't exist.\NYou don't survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.40,0:35:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the ego is constantly that quality of life which samples everything experientially\Nto discern is it pro-life or anti-life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.36,0:36:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the kinesiologic response then, if it's over 200, the life energy gets that this is pro-life,\Nand she goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.13,0:36:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's anti-life, below 200, the little proto, the little amoeba in her senses that and goes weak.\NIt says, no, don't eat that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.79,0:36:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's automatized over the millennia in the autonomic nervous system\Nand in the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.67,0:36:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I hold something in mind, I don't even have to tell her what it is.\NSo, I'm going to hold something in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.20,0:36:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind calibrates over 400, 450, 480, 475.\NIt's a painting by Degas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.54,0:36:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And she doesn't know what I was holding in mind.\NYou can see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.04,0:37:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A painting by Degas of the ballet dancers, you know, a very entrancing impressionistic painting.\NCalibrates at 480.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.44,0:37:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see how life then evolved over time, calibrated level of life overall.\NThe first signs of life were then bacteria and algae calibrated at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.67,0:37:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And marine invertebrates, cephalopods, and then we go up to the mammalian life.\NCalibrated level of evolution, calibrated level of life over the eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.69,0:37:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next next slide.\NSo, here you see bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.48,0:37:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we said, what is the lowest level that we can say life emerges as bacteria?\NWe'll call that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.10,0:37:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the highest it reaches?\NAnd we found that at 1,000, the great avatars, Jesus Christ, Buddha, Krishna,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.10,0:38:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Zoroaster, all calibrated at 1,000.\NHighest energy of life experientially in this world, therefore, are the great avatars at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.69,0:38:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They represent, therefore,\NIn this range is the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.86,0:38:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's nothing relativist hate worse than the thought of an absolute.\NBecause their idea of reality is reality is whatever you think it is, and project out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.08,0:38:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They think that perception is reality.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.02,0:38:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,These numbers are all essence.\NPerception is not reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.08,0:38:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence is reality.\NIf anything is only what you think it is, then there is no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.88,0:38:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's no reality, then there's no reality to their statement, that,\NThere is no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.56,0:38:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get rid of deconstructionism is you can deconstruct deconstructionism, because\Nthe premise is that all premises are false, that means the premise is that all things
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.02,0:39:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,are false is false, so that's the end of relativism.\NNo, the absolute, some people have reviewed some of my work somewhere, and he warns the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.97,0:39:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,reader, beware, he's an absolutist.\NAutism means responsibility, doesn't it, means yes, you are accountable, yeah, means
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.66,0:39:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your karma is what counts, all right.\NSo here we go, you see protozoa, crustaceans, insects, amphibians, did anybody see the Blue
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.43,0:39:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Planet the other night?\NThe Blue Planet reruns on TV, if you haven't seen the Blue Planet, be sure to see it, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.43,0:39:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so stunningly beautiful, and people who don't believe in intelligent design, I tell them,\Nwatch the Blue Planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.03,0:39:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then call me later.\NAnd tell me if you still don't believe in intelligent design, the exquisite beauty and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.43,0:39:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute perfection of the evolution of all things at the bottom of the sea, mysterious\Nand entrancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.77,0:40:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch these little things down there, they're incredible beauty, and their ingenuity,\Nthis little diddly light gets you to bite and come over and try and eat me, and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.69,0:40:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you, smarts.\NUnintelligent life is nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.92,0:40:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It killed itself off millennia ago.\NThere's only intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.68,0:40:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, arachnids, the fish, you see, the octopus, I love the octopus, they're the smartest\Nthing around, 20, and you see the Komodo dragon, don't go in the cage with them, and if you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.65,0:40:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,do, always wear your shoes, some idiot went in the cage with a Komodo dragon without his\Nshoes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.80,0:40:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he lived to tell the tale, God bless him.\NSnakes and alligators, and all kinds of wiggly, screamy things, dinosaurs, whales, dolphins,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.32,0:41:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,whales, and all these kind of things, aha.\NSo down here you see dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.34,0:41:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know that there are a large percentage of people on the planet that are at this level,\Nthat of the reptile, reptile, there are actually people out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.38,0:41:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,These serial killers that kill lots of children, they calibrate at 35, less than a reptile, aha.\NNow you notice that life in here has to destroy other life in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.54,0:41:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The polar bears got to pounce on a seal and eat it.\NAll these animals here, wolves and all these, live by killing others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.30,0:41:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at level about 200, you see the emergence of the herbivores.\NAnd who do not have to kill anything in order to live, they live on vegetation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.24,0:42:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so here you see a shift from carnivorous predators to benign, the grazers, deer and\Ndomestic pigs and elk, dairy cows, the sheep, range cattle, and now we're getting over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.28,0:42:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very interesting.\NNow we're very, very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.21,0:42:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can relate to these animals.\NAnd elephants at 235.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.43,0:42:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NA kitty is at 240, and a family kitty that's loved is 245.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.92,0:42:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs at 245.\NThen we go up through the monkeys, the gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.25,0:42:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex, the trained African great parrot, is at 400.\NCoco, the trained gorilla, is at 405.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.08,0:42:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you realize you are safer in a cage with Coco than 90% of the people on this planet?\NCoco's not out to do you any harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.82,0:43:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not trying to sell you anything, isn't going to kill you in the name of peace.\NCoco says, either be peaceful or I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.70,0:43:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the most amazing thing, and we still don't have the answer, is a cat's purr calibrates\Nat 500, which is the level of love, as does a dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.11,0:43:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They have literally the capacity to love.\NThat's why when I hear a cat's purr, I'm like, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.13,0:43:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.\NI had a practice, and I would have a depressed patient living alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.45,0:43:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, I'm not going to treat you unless you get her a cat or a dog.\NYou need something to think about except your own self all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.17,0:43:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cat's purr at 500 and the dog's wagging tail at 500.\NAmazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.33,0:43:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, kinesiology is very useful.\NWe use it all the time because you can know the unknowable.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.23,0:43:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can know the unknowable.\NRight now, we've got a sick kitty at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.26,0:43:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I can find out his medication.\NLet's check out kitty at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.29,0:43:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We can check out kitty at home right now.\NRight now, he's feeling comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.29,0:43:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NHe's got pain, but the medication is handling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.29,0:43:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we should keep the dose of the medication the same.\NGive it to him every other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.42,0:44:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs antibiotics right now.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.42,0:44:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NDo we have them on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.42,0:44:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.09,0:44:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.09,0:44:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.09,0:44:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.09,0:44:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.09,0:44:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.16,0:44:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.16,0:44:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.57,0:44:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.57,0:44:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.76,0:44:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.84,0:44:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.84,0:44:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.99,0:44:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.99,0:44:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that saved a big bill at the veterinarian, didn't it?\NI think he might be anemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.99,0:44:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil, let me check here.\NHe has clinical anemia, is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.99,0:44:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I knew he would get it.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.99,0:44:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, he's got a bleeding lesion, he's got anemia.\NSo he's a little cat, but we've got the diagnosis on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.35,0:44:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We know everything we need to know about him.\NWe know whether he operates, if we raise him on medication, his pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.09,0:44:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can know the unknowable.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.99,0:45:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, many things in your life will become unknowable and now you have a way to instantly know the\Ntruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.48,0:45:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have permission to ask the question.\NSo, I don't always verbalize it in front of an audience because it's on repetition,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.00,0:45:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but I ask before I ask it, I have permission to ask this question.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.48,0:45:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't need it.\NI have permission to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.20,0:45:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And occasionally, we will get a no, and in fact, we've gotten no in front of large audiences\Nand we didn't know the reason for the no and we didn't have time to research it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.30,0:45:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's probably some things that are better not to know.\NGot in his wisdom, keeps us ignorant of certain things, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.68,0:45:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on to the next.\NNow the thing that's, okay, this is the relationship between the linear and the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.87,0:45:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThe linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.71,0:46:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The linear is like science.\NIt's discernible and it operates according to, or it seems to operate according to Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.93,0:46:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,principles of cause and effect.\NIt's definable, identifiable, it's a world of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.18,0:46:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world, the Newtonian world of causality.\NHowever, what the Newtonian world of causality ignored until just recently in quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.05,0:46:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it doesn't exist in a vacuum.\NIt exists in a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.39,0:46:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite field.\NInfinite field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.46,0:46:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only reason the linear works is because of the power of the infinite field of the\Nnonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.23,0:46:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you take a potentiality all by itself, something that's linear, nothing will happen\Nunless you, you know, you might say electrify it, put it in an infinite field of power,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.46,0:46:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and now that which is intention becomes an actuality.\NSo things come about then.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.64,0:47:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of a karmic emergence, karmic too, karmic and karmic, the emergence of potentiality\Ndepending on local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.52,0:47:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore your own intention has a very powerful effect.\NThe less selfish the intention, the greater the likelihood that it will manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.56,0:47:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you, to want, crave, desire, and gotta have, tends to block it, tends to block it.\NTo hold it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.36,0:47:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Every place I've lived all the last, well, a lot of years now, well over 50 years, every\Nplace that I've lived, I had only envisioned, I just pictured what I thought, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.38,0:47:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would really love to have, and it would always just magically appear, where I live now, was\Nthe same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.72,0:47:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I just held in mind that which would be ideal, and the next thing you know, somebody would\Ncall me and say, you know what, there's a property next door to me and it's for sale,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.68,0:48:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how the place I live now came about.\NAnd back east, I just envisioned a place in the woods and a place in the woods came about.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.54,0:48:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you hold in mind then tends to manifest because there's an infinite field, which\Nis consciousness, divinity, you might say, the omnipotence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.40,0:48:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The proximate field is what you're holding in mind, proximate field.\NAnd then the content is, let's say, you want a house or a car, a pretty maiden, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.90,0:48:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever.\NWe'll move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.42,0:48:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The content then, we say, is the ego, it's linear, it's measurable.\NThe spiritual ego, here's the nonlinear dynamics and the quantum mechanics, the context is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.38,0:48:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit, which is nonlinear, unlimited, self-existent, we call it spiritual.\NIt's demonstrable, we demonstrate it using kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.77,0:49:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what's the next one now?\NI forget what number we're on.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.88,0:49:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Eighteen.\NEighteen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.51,0:49:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NWhere's my magnifying glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.80,0:49:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a magnifying glass.\NHow am I going to see what's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.34,0:49:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway, things get dimmer as you get older, I don't know, it's just that the universe\Ndoes that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.44,0:49:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe gets dimmer.\NIt has nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.48,0:49:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What number are we at?\NEighteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.15,0:49:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, eighteen.\NOkay, so, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.33,0:49:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, somebody's got to keep track of the time.\NWe'll have to take a break at what time?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.59,0:49:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Five more minutes.\NOh, my god.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.59,0:49:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I better hurry up.\NAlright.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.59,0:49:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics, because it's important to understand quantum mechanics.\NYou can't become enlightened without quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.76,0:50:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Schrodinger equations denote the current state of the universe.\NThrough the Heisenberg principle, you make a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.15,0:50:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you collapse the wave function, and you do it via the von Neumann process, and\Nthen by calculating the Dirac, you can calculate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.15,0:50:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the potentiality then becomes an actuality via the Heisenberg process.\NThat was the discovery, that you cannot do the same experiment twice, because merely
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.22,0:50:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing and observing an experiment already changes the outcome, the introduction of consciousness.\NSo, Stapp is the most advanced physicist in my idea of understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.90,0:51:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as we teach, everything is in a state of potentiality awaiting to be collapsed into\Nan actuality, collapse the wave function from potentiality into actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.12,0:51:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what you hold in mind tends to manifest.\NSo, you picture yourself in whatever condition you think would be ideal, and let go of one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.12,0:51:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the two.\NYou want it, desire it, or crave it, and you surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.49,0:51:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of trying to make it happen, you allow it to happen.\NSo, spiritual work is not yang, it's yin.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.91,0:51:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say every position that I've advanced through this lifetime has been a yin.\NTo thee, O Lord, do I surrender my will in the matter, instead of yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.48,0:51:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the ego is very yang and very linear.\NAnd it is out there on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.84,0:51:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The yin, now.\NThe thing is, as you know from the 91st Psalm, in the statement of Krishna, those who call
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.16,0:52:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,upon me are mine, and God cannot refuse you.\NGod is unable to refuse your legitimate appeal or resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.58,0:52:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.\NYou ever hear that one before?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.48,0:52:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NSo, that which supplicates infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.11,0:52:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If infinity then is almost, well, it's the wrong word, but obligated, you might say,\Nto respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.39,0:52:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you may get a no, because of your own karmic propensity.\NSo, on the way down from 13,000 feet, you can undo a lot of negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.79,0:53:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the end, you probably, that got rid of the last of that negative karma.\NAll the people you killed all over your lifetimes, you look at the history of mankind and think
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.75,0:53:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people you probably killed in previous lifetimes.\NKilling others was the way life was, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.61,0:53:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Vikings came over, they didn't capture slaves, they slaughtered them all.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.61,0:53:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Visigoths, the history of mankind is you slaughter your enemies.\NConsequently, the karmic inheritance of mankind, then, has to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.93,0:53:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, has to do with the undoing of a good deal of manslaughter.\NIf you have permission to ask this, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.93,0:53:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That is true, oh Lord, resist.\NYeah, the undoing of a good deal of negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.93,0:53:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Say to yourself as you break your leg or whatever, well, that gets rid of that negative karma.\NThat gets rid of that negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.18,0:53:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything serves the purpose of evolution.\NThis is a perfect world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.18,0:54:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to gain karmic merit, you have to have the option of making a mistake and refuse the mistake\Nand this time choose correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.18,0:54:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, there's no karmic merit, right?\NIsn't that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.18,0:54:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in your karmic bank account is going up and going down.\NAnd, of course, so this world is a world that is perfect for the evolution of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.44,0:54:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to go from the lower levels, the linear, the animal instincts, to shift from this side of the brain,\Nyou pray to the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.12,0:54:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking for the kundalini energy to rise.\NThe kundalini energy then rises and as it does, it shifts your whole perception of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.12,0:54:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The world looks differently.\NYou all look friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.24,0:54:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here is friendly.\NIf there isn't anybody who's not here and is not friendly, I'll beat them up until they're friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.45,0:55:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat them until they are friendly.\NWho is that king that would beat his subjects until they loved him?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.61,0:55:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll beat him until he loves me.\NSo, we attract to ourselves that which we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.84,0:55:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, when we leave the body, where do we go?\NWe go to that which we already are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.84,0:55:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it. I have permission to ask that.\NThat is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.93,0:55:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about it after death because you're only going to go to that which you already are.\NYou can't go to something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.67,0:55:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all like little magnetic filings in a great electrostatic field.\NSo, you automatically go to that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.89,0:55:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by free choice, by option, you say yes to this option, like a little piece of iron filing.\NYour positive end and you got a negative end.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.89,0:56:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you choose love like this and you choose hate there, you choose love.\NSo, like a little iron filing, you can see your spirit is constantly moving, shifting in an infinite field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.89,0:56:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Which we call God.\NTherefore, the justice of God is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.40,0:56:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not arbitrary.\NNot a cranky old man who gets mad at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.64,0:56:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The justice of God is automatic.\NIn an infinite electromagnetic field, there is no injustice.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.00,0:56:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single little filing is exactly where it is based on its polarity.\NAnd as you say yes, oh, heck with it, I'll forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.03,0:56:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You move to this side.\NYou say, son of a bitch, I want to kill that bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.03,0:56:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You move to this side.\NAnd you can see where you are is the consequence of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.35,0:57:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, there's no point to fear an arbitrary God who's like a nasty old crank.\NThe God of the Old Testament is, you know, an anthropomorphic weirdo, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.37,0:57:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, gets all jealous, upset, has his favorites, plays favorite.\NYou don't need a God for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.50,0:57:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Your next door neighbor is a...\NYou know, Freud ridiculed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.65,0:57:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, I agree with Freud about that myself.\NThe anthropomorphic understandings of God are in predictions of the child-parent relationship from the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.78,0:57:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud then made the mistake, if there's no false God, therefore there's no true God.\NSo, Freud calibrated 499, genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.20,0:57:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But he didn't get to 500.\NAnd the fact that the false depictions of God are false doesn't mean that the true ones are not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.20,0:57:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he jumped beyond the level of logic.\NAnd, of course, I myself was psychoanalyzed.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.20,0:57:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And my analyst...\NFreud was really my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.20,0:58:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My analyst was Lionel Oversee, whose analyst was analyzed by Freud.\NSo, Freud's my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.20,0:58:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a Freudian analysis.\NI was very young then.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.20,0:58:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I saw Harry Thiebaud, who was the foremost psychoanalyst in analyzing the ego and the unconscious.\NAnd you just brought in dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.20,0:58:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I had about three different kinds of psychoanalysis.\NAnd then spent the next 50 years listening to some 25,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.20,0:58:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,25,000 people from a psychiatric, psychoanalytic, psychological viewpoint and treating that many.\NAnd the way I'm describing things is a composite of that totality of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.92,0:58:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychoanalytic.\NI also had experiences, which I've written about in books, which were unusual, starting at age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.92,0:59:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I got enough time for that?\NYes or no?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.71,0:59:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just do a brief one, and then we'll have a quick break.\NBut this lifetime was unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.96,0:59:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Statistically, I guess.\NAnyway, there was absolute oblivion until age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.35,0:59:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Age three, out of oblivion, out of the oblivion of nothingness, suddenly there occurred, with a terrible shock, the awareness of existence.\NFrom nothingness to existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.35,0:59:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a terrible shock.\NA severe shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.35,0:59:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I still haven't gotten over it.\NEvery once in a while, I rediscover that I exist, and it comes back as a shock again.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.08,0:59:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in many lifetimes, I was a Hinayana Buddhist.\NI negated the linear, and I would go into the void, and I would leave that lifetime in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.11,1:00:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, at age three, suddenly I came into the awareness of existence.\NExistence versus nonexistence was the puzzle and the conundrum of this entire lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.11,1:00:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not pleased to discover I exist.\NA three-year-old body.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.84,1:00:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only did you exist, but a body went with it.\NA three-year-old body sitting in a wagon.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.77,1:00:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all nonverbal.\NJust a stunning awareness of existence as existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.73,1:00:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then came, as soon as you realize you exist, up comes the fear of nonexistence.\NInstantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.86,1:00:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you identify with existence as a reality, you instantly are stuck with the fear of nonexistence.\NSo at age three, there I was, stuck with the conundrum of, is the infinite reality existence or nonexistence?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.86,1:00:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't solve that one until consciousness level 850.\NIt took some 30 years to solve that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.30,1:00:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.\NWhat was I telling you this for?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.16,1:00:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.\NWhat was I going to tell him?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.16,1:01:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.\NI was brought up very, very religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.16,1:01:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Episcopal, high Episcopal.\NMy great-grandfather was an Episcopal bishop.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.26,1:01:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very religious.\NAnd I was very religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.45,1:01:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I suffered from scrupulosity.\NI worried about having a sin all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.45,1:01:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\NI thought the soul was like a big blank screen, and if you sinned, it blotched up there,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.45,1:01:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody threw an egg on it, and God would see this sin on your soul.\NSo I was scared to death of having a sin that God was going to see, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.45,1:01:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God's looking at your soul, and here you got all these black spots on your soul.\NSo if I had any kind of a negative thought, I really had a fit about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.48,1:01:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to go for counseling about it.\N. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.67,1:01:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in fear of sin.\NI was an acolyte in church, you know, and I was an acolyte for the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.99,1:02:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,church, you know, and I was an acolyte for the bishop. And I was a boy soprano, an excellent\Nboy soprano, stunningly good boy soprano. Well, you can say that when you're objective
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.83,1:02:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,about yourself. And I sang in the Greek choir, and I was the boy soloist. And when I sang\Nthe soprano obbligato above a full choir, paunus angelicus, with a full choir, a full
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.22,1:02:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,orchestra, and a full organ, it was entrancing. It was entrancing to the witness because while\Npeople presume I'm a me, I'm not a me, I'm the witness. And so, I remember witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.99,1:02:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the voice coming out. It was as though an angelic being sang through the voice. The\Naudience went into tears, and I don't know how I continued to sing, but I did so. I never
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.71,1:03:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,asked this before.\NI've got permission to ask this. That was indeed an angelic being. So, yes, an angelic
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.34,1:03:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,voice. It's a stunning beauty. Later on, I joined the Great Lakes Naval Choir. In World\NWar II, I signed up for the Navy. I forget how I became an atheist. Somehow or other.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.56,1:03:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, then, about age 13.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.56,1:03:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIn the way out in the sticks of Wisconsin. I had the longest paper route in Wisconsin,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.78,1:03:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and 18 miles every day, 10 below zero on the bicycle. And in a very high storm one day,\Na very high storm. It was 10 below zero. I mean, it was ferocious. All my papers are
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.13,1:03:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,blown away, and it's pitch black out. There isn't any light of a farmhouse for miles ahead\Nyet. And to get out of this cold, I dug a hole in the snow. Well, the banks in the Wisconsin
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.30,1:03:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,highways are probably 15 feet high by the end of the day. And I was in the middle of\Nthe snow. I was in the middle of the snow. I was in the middle of the snow. I was in
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.82,1:04:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the winter, around late winter. So, I broke through the crust of the snow, and I made\Na little cave, and I climbed into the cave to get out of the wind, get of the wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.31,1:04:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as I got out of the wind, all of a sudden a state of infinite presence.\NEverything became silent beyond all time. That which I am existed before all time, before
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.78,1:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all worlds, and will exist beyond all\Nall worlds. That which I am was before all worlds resist and will be after all worlds
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.80,1:05:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,resist. That knowingness of foreverness. And I understood then, not intellectually, but\Nthe experience of timelessness. That which has no beginning has no ending. The sense
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.34,1:05:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of love was overwhelming. It's an infinite presence of the Self with a capital S. People\Nsay, how do I know I'm enlightened? Because the presence wipes out everything. There's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.08,1:05:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,no thought, there's nothing. There's only in that which you are, is that, is not different\Nthan what you are. That moment, all fear of death disappeared forever, which was handy
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.72,1:06:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in World War II, when you're about to get blown up. About to get blown up. Yes?\NWe'll, we'll quit with the World War II. Yeah. You're about to get blown up any second.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.21,1:06:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can remember, here's this mine right there, and these big things are sticking off\Nthis mine, and it's about to bump against the ship. And this, this guy's supposed to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.39,1:06:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,help me. We're supposed to keep this mine from hitting the ship, because they're all\Ngoing to blow up. He says, so, what if it blows up? I said, well, then we die. He said,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.01,1:06:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, you're right. And that was the end of the fear.\NTotal acceptance of death, then. Now, as if you want to evolve rapidly, handle death
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.48,1:06:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the beginning. Don't leave it to the end. You decide I'll wait until I'm 85,\Nand then I'll face that one. Do it right now. Because underneath all the negative feelings
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.94,1:06:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you see from consciousness level below 200, underneath all of them is death. So if you\Nstart with death, if I'm not successful, then what? Then I'll be poor. And if you're poor,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.46,1:06:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then what? Then I won't be able to afford what I need. Yes. And then what? And then\NI'll be poor. And if you're poor, then what? Then I won't be able to afford what I need.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.94,1:07:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I will die. You'll find that every one of them ends up, and then I'll die. So start\Nby dying and get that over with. How many people here have been out of body? Yep, great.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.04,1:07:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Near death experiences. Yep, very good. All right, so people who have near death experiences\Nor out of body experiences are better prepared to die because you've experienced that you
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.20,1:07:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,are, even though the body's laying there. In fact, it's odd. When you're out of the\Nbody, the body looks totally uninteresting. It looks really stupid, and you have to get
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.68,1:07:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,back in it because you're not karmically free to go yet. But I can remember looking at it\Nand thinking, man, that is really not too attractive. I went back in it upside down,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.96,1:07:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at the floor through the back of my skull, had to pull myself out of the body\Nand re-dock.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.30,1:08:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a good place that we're going to take a break. I was telling you my sad tale\Nof, let's see, where was I? World War II, I think. Anyway, I was very, as I say, spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.82,1:08:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,oriented. And one day, the war was over, one day walking around in the woods thinking of\Nnothing at all, not thinking of anything. All of a sudden, out of nowhere, came an infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.54,1:08:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness of infinite dimension of the totality of the suffering of all of mankind\Nsince the beginning, since the beginning. The totality of the suffering of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.98,1:09:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was like a presentation, a knowingness that came upon me. It was so overwhelming. I thought,\Nany God who could allow this, I want nothing to do with, and I became an atheist. From
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.38,1:09:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,an intensely religious point of view, I became an atheist. I became an atheist. I became\Na person, I became a devoted atheist. Any God who could allow that quantity of suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.71,1:09:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was no God in my book. And I rejected God and I became an atheist. So, that time I was\Ngoing to a Jesuit university and I got straight A in everything. I didn't believe a word of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.61,1:09:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it. I got a straight A in the subject, you know. Why? Because if you're going to argue\Nagainst something, you better know a great deal about it. The critics of my own work,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.94,1:09:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have that feeling. They don't know anything about it, so what they say is babbling, but\Nanyway, you've got to understand everything about it. So, I got straight A in all those
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.96,1:10:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,things. But there had to be some inner essence of truth, and therefore, I devoted myself\Nto the search for the essence of truth without God. I studied Buddhism and all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.32,1:10:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I belonged to the first Zen Institute in New York. Actually, I finally became a consultant\Nto
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.53,1:10:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of religious orders, Catholic orders, Protestant, Episcopal Diocese, and the Zen\NMonastery upstate New York, because I had, by that time, some rather profound experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.53,1:10:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could discern whether the person was in a catatonic state or a Samadhi. I forgot\Nhow it all went. But in the search for truth then became an obsession. And if the essence
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.49,1:10:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth wasn't God, then what was it?\NAnd so, I went to the very core of the source of consciousness itself. The exploration took
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.95,1:11:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,me through really Dante's inferno. It eventually took me to the levels of hell. And the levels\Nof hell are far beyond that which can be imagined, far more dreadful, far more worse. You enter
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.51,1:11:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,finally a realm, and Dante understood it. I don't know how Dante knew it. There's a\Nlevel of hell that you can't really imagine. You enter a realm, and you have to take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.23,1:11:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a level of hell that you can't really imagine. There's a level of hell that you can't\Nof hell where abandon all hope you enter here because you then enter a state of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.88,1:11:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,timelessness so you were like damned you were cut off into hopelessness and\Ndespair forever and you get what forever means and that is when hell really
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.54,1:12:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,starts cut off forever from love from God from salvation in a state of\Nspiritual agony from which there is no release ever so timelessness just as in
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.18,1:12:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest states you're beyond all time in the lowest state you again go\Nback into timelessness which is beyond all description eternal agony in the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.00,1:12:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,depth of eternal agony\Nthe atheist said if there is a God I ask him for help and then I was hit by like
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.72,1:13:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a bolt of lightning all that it ever had been disappeared and instead what shone\Nforth was the glory divinity as existence itself the whole world became
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.66,1:13:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,radiant with exquisite beauty to which it has remained except you get\Nused to it because otherwise you can't function and I'm having difficulty
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.26,1:13:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,functioning this morning because of the state is very close again so glad you\Ndid there help out a little bit here okay thank you the infinite states are
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.72,1:13:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,so past the void which is consciousness level 850 oh I know I was going to say\Nthat the way you get to the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.81,1:14:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,void which I kept going out of previous lifetimes in the void because I follow\Nthe pathway of negation pathway of negation will eventually take you to the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.56,1:14:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,void at level 850 is nothingness as the ultimate reality it is so impressive so\Nawesome that you are sure that this is the state of enlightenment itself
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.66,1:14:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Huang Po made the same mistake and\Nbut having been in the infinite presence in the snowbank I realized that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.27,1:14:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness was devoid of something incredibly essential and therefore I\Nrefused the void this time because the infinite reality is the overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.15,1:15:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of an infinite love so the nothingness of the void you reject its\Nreality when you get to nothingness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.50,1:15:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,reject the nothingness because divinity is allness infinite love and the owning\Nof that takes you past the 850 and Huang Po made the same mistake when he
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.72,1:15:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote it calibrates at 850 the path to the occlusion. Huang Po after writing that\Ndiscovered his error so before he died he went to 960 I'm happy to say for Huang
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.96,1:15:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Po\NAnyway, that's neither here nor there, so where were we on the slides?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.59,1:15:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,After that everything, oh yes, after that everything happens autonomously and you realize\Nthe narcissistic, the idea that there's a separate you that's a causal agent is the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.44,1:16:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,delusion that one overcomes to reach enlightenment.\NThere is no you that is making decisions and causing things to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.16,1:16:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening autonomously of its own.\NEverything is continuously.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.14,1:16:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality is constantly emerging.\NThere's no me that decided, oh, I think I'll put my arm up in the air to make that point.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.53,1:16:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It had already happened before I noticed it was there.\NIf you get, it's a one ten-thousandth of a second jump that you have to get on the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.48,1:16:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer aspect of the ego instantly takes credit.\NIt says, ah, there was an I that made that decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.24,1:16:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no I that makes that decision.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.56,1:16:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just said is the truth, oh Lord, resist.\NWhat I just said is the truth, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.04,1:17:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't swear by the Lord unless it's the absolute truth.\NThere is no personal self that's making all the decisions over which you agonize.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.77,1:17:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it is happening autonomously, autonomously.\NThe consequent of that which you are interacts with potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.40,1:17:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And out comes the decision.\NI can be as free as I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.16,1:17:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do what I want.\NAnd if you don't like it, then how do you like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.38,1:17:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anybody decide to say that?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.86,1:17:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the states of spiritual awareness, people forget to go through joy, ecstasy.\NIn fact, they can become paralyzing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.44,1:17:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,States of extreme ecstasy can become paralyzing.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.80,1:17:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Paralyzed, you're tireless.\NYou can dance for hours and hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.65,1:17:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can dance tirelessly.\NYou can dance around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.13,1:18:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You never go to the bathroom.\NYou don't need a drink of water, water, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.13,1:18:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You just go into a state.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.62,1:18:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramakrishna experienced such ecstatic states.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.62,1:18:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate around 580, 590, around in there.\NSo you go into all these states of consciousness, and if you've heard about them before, it's
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.20,1:18:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful because you don't feel strange, you don't feel like something is unusual or there's\Nsomething wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.61,1:18:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh, that's right.\NIt's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.07,1:18:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay for that to be what it is.\NSo we'll go back to the academics.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.44,1:18:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd just make a few personal remarks to break up the monotony here.\NAs I said, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.70,1:18:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.80,1:19:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI mean, the Kundalini energy is an actual spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.03,1:19:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People below 200, you realize, have sort of a group karma.\NAnd it's only from 200 and up that you develop an etheric body, an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.44,1:19:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That seems unfair.\NYou only develop an etheric brain when consciousness level 200 exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.78,1:19:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, people don't have an etheric brain yet.\NSo you want them to understand spiritual concepts.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.20,1:19:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When they don't have the equipment, you can't understand that goodwill is more important\Nthan killing and getting even.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.87,1:19:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any sense until you get to level 200, and then you say, oh yes, that's\Nobvious, that's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.81,1:19:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not obvious below 200.\NAnybody who gives up their life for another is stupid below 200, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.02,1:20:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so, below consciousness level 200, left brain dominance, you're living in\Na linear world, fight or flight, the alarm reaction, the thymus gland, the acupuncture
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.71,1:20:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,meridians, everything is now controlled by the left brain.\NYou notice in the left brain, animal world, people below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.51,1:20:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the input.\NThe relay is very fast to the emotional center, the thalamus, very fast to the emotional
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.29,1:20:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,center.\NThe amygdala, the hippocampus, your memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.71,1:20:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So your memory is of a fearful, frightening, angry, embarrassing.\NIt's a negative viewpoint of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.29,1:20:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,From 200 down, hate, anger, greed, selfishness, jealousy, envy, dominate.\NSo this is the world of the animal pack, and if you watch international political maneuverings,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.09,1:21:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it's no different at all than a wolf pack.\NAlpha male, jostling for alpha male, constantly pushing for more territory.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.11,1:21:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You urinate on all these bushes over here, and once you're there, come over.\NAnd if you do, oh, so you see that primarily the world lives on an animal level.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.22,1:21:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more dominance of more and more territory, so you're the alpha male, and you can have\Nall the alpha females, and if you're lucky, you can do this for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.40,1:21:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, how boring it is.\NImagine that heaven where all you do is fornicate all day.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.20,1:21:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, century after century, you say, God, how am I going to have to keep fornicating?\NI'm tired of beautiful females, so I have to keep doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.99,1:22:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you wanted to do it, man, so, I mean, you know, hysterical.\NLife is one eternal orgasm, isn't that hysterical?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.46,1:22:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, you give up eternal orgasm.\NIt's a fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.18,1:22:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to our...\NGod's either pleased or not pleased, I don't know what it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.25,1:22:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's pleased, okay.\NThe kundalini begins to follow up the chakra system, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.07,1:22:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now right brain dominance, now context, the nonlinear domain, meaning and significance.\NYour brain puts out endorphins instead of adrenaline, positive emotions, the thymus
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.34,1:22:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,gland, increased killer cells, so you're less prone to diseases.\NIncreased blood pressure.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.54,1:22:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Increased healing, balancing the acupuncture system.\NAnd the track to the emotions is now slowed down.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.53,1:22:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more enlightened person, 200 and up, you get a fast track through the etheric brain,\Nwhich is the capacity to see the essence of a thing, very fast, through the emotional
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.29,1:23:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,center, and your memory is of a very wonderful and positive experience.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.97,1:23:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I experienced this audience, it was very wonderful and positive, you know, period.\NExperience.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.71,1:23:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because I see the essence of things.\NSo obviously, an audience like this calibrates over 200, so I pick up the positive essence
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.70,1:23:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of this audience, and you feel happy and content because you're surrounded by that which is\Nsafety and loving, supportive, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.13,1:23:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on.\NI just wanted to point out that there's an actual physiologic difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.95,1:23:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the rates of enlightenment...\NOr happiness, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.40,1:23:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If we start at the bottom, calibrated at level 20, the number...\NThe percent of people who are happy at these various consciousness levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.62,1:23:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So happiness is not a consequence of the world and what you have in the world and what you\Ndo in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.00,1:24:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a consequence of that which you have become.\NIf you have become this, then the likelihood of happiness is close to 70%.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.01,1:24:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, then, is not a socio-economic class or political trauma.\NIt's a consequence of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.43,1:24:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When you become the fulfillment of your potential, you're happy no matter what.\NYou're happy no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.52,1:24:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So at this low level, these are criminal populations here, criminal populations.\NYou see, at log 20, only 1% of people are happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.40,1:24:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.36,1:24:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NPeople who live in the world of guilt and penance, you see, at consciousness level 30,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.92,1:25:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,4% are happy.\NSackcloth and ashes was the sort of medieval way to God through Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.77,1:25:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, forgive me my evil and guilt.\NAnd you kneel and crawl on your knees all the way to the cathedral, beating on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.08,1:25:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, that's real narcissism, isn't it?\N.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.34,1:25:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's real drama.\NOh, God, I am such a sinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.34,1:25:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break, will you?\NWallowing in guilt and penance is sort of a medieval.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.34,1:25:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Medieval.\NAnd it's one of the reasons I gave up Christianity when I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.34,1:25:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't see wallowing in guilt and penance.\NI mean, you know, if man can't tell truth from falsehood, I mean, whatever happened
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.14,1:25:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Garden of Eden, I mean, I don't have anything to do with it.\NI mean, I don't have anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.14,1:25:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.14,1:25:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.14,1:25:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.24,1:25:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.24,1:25:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.24,1:25:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NYou know, if man can't tell truth from falsehood, I mean, whatever happened in the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.72,1:25:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Garden, you know, of Eden, I mean, I don't have anything to do with it.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.51,1:26:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My toy, you know what I'm saying?\NThe serpent took advantage of the fact that the human mind, unaided, is unable to discern
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.99,1:26:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.\NUnaided.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.67,1:26:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind, by virtue of its structure.\Ncannot tell appearance from essence. Socrates said it. All men choose only the good. A lot
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.78,1:26:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of times we feel guilty because we find it difficult to forgive somebody. See? Christ\Nsaid forgive them all, they know not what they do, etc. The Buddha said the only difficulty
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.84,1:26:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with everyone is ignorance. So you remind yourself of that profound innate ignorance.\NThat's built into the ego structure as it evolved. The ego is unable to discern appearance
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.23,1:26:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,from essence. It's only consciousness level 600, the opening of the third eye of the Buddhic\Nbody, the third body, that one discerns essence rather than appearance. So the value of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.11,1:27:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration is you can accomplish what the human mind cannot do. The human mind looks\Nat a thing, it doesn't know whether that's gold or fool's gold. Instantly with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.73,1:27:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what it is. So it bypasses. All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.94,1:27:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.98,1:27:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.06,1:27:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.14,1:27:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.26,1:27:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.30,1:27:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.48,1:27:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.58,1:27:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.24,1:27:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.36,1:27:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.78,1:27:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 5% say they're happy. Those who live in fear, 10%. Those who are angry,\Nonly 12% of those people are happy. And they're probably retarded or something, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.57,1:27:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride at least makes sense. Log 175, 22%. That makes sense, you know. At least you're\Nhappy that you're better than other people and all that. Everybody secretly believes
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.10,1:27:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that their view of reality is correct and everybody else's is wrong.\NDon't we all?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.10,1:27:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All in favor of I'm right and everybody else is wrong.\NYay, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.90,1:28:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get rid of the ego unless you own it.\NYes, the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.18,1:28:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It just loves being right.\NAnd it's willing to be right even if it costs you your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.22,1:28:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWhen you get beyond pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.98,1:28:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know that pride is where so many things fall.\NIt's where all the great dictators, if they aren't crazy,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.59,1:28:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,before they get there, they're crazy after they get there.\NBecause of the pride, the narcissistic ego just goes crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.96,1:28:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, at 200 is the capacity to tell the truth.\NThat's the first in the 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.88,1:28:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's step one.\NWe admitted we were powerless over something.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.92,1:28:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Admitted you were powerless over?\NWow, what an affront to the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.36,1:28:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego isn't going to admit it's powerless.\NIt's going to admit it's powerless over anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.50,1:28:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to control it and make it different this time.\NAt 200, then you enter the world of honesty.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.76,1:29:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,At level 200, 55% of people are happy.\NAnd neutrality, you move beyond courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.71,1:29:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutrality is it's okay if it happens this way and it's okay if it happens that way.\NIf I get the job, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.40,1:29:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I don't, I'll get another job.\NSo neutral is very comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.28,1:29:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fun being with neutral people because they're easygoing.\NAnd 60% of them are happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.88,1:29:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NThe other 40% have bad spouses or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.31,1:29:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NThere's some defect in this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.85,1:29:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you're really at neutral, you'd be happy under any circumstance.\NSo we'll have to reexamine that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.31,1:29:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been in neutral and it's okay, you know.\NYou know, like I say, a bomb is about to go off.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.03,1:29:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The mine is about to explode.\NAnd it goes off, it goes off.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.45,1:29:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it doesn't, it doesn't.\NSo what's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.69,1:30:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Either die or you don't.\NSo willingness is a positive attitude at 310, but 68% of the people,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.27,1:30:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the people that help make the world, they're humanitarians.\NThey sign up for all kinds of help things, clean up Katrina after Katrina,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.93,1:30:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all these kind of things.\NAcceptance is the beginning of the only owning of your power at 350, 71%.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.61,1:30:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason is the world of the world.\NIt's the world of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.77,1:30:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't do the great books of the Western world, did we?\NWell, we'll have to do them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.90,1:30:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason now is the beginning of the advances of Western civilization as we understand it,\Nis the level of the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.90,1:30:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world are at the 400s.\NOn the slide, see if you can find the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.90,1:30:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll just flick to it later on.\NAnyway, it's the intellectual backbone.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.37,1:30:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the intellectual backbone.\NIt's the intellectual backbone.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.54,1:31:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the intellectual backbone of Western civilization begins with Plato, Aristotle.\NTo my viewpoint, the highest evolution of human civilization was around 350 BC,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.56,1:31:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's been downhill ever since, frankly.\NTo forgive everybody is easy if you accept Socrates' wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.96,1:31:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone chooses only the good, you know, what they think to be the good.\NSo, everyone is only choosing what they...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.72,1:31:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see the innocence that they think that will bring them fame and happiness and,\Nyou know, whatever they do, which is outrageous on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.43,1:31:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But if, you know...\NSo, anyway, neutrality, it's okay if it goes this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.29,1:31:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingness is joining in, and acceptance is even higher.\NAnd reason is the intellect, and this is the bulwark of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.29,1:32:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s then takes you through the great books.\NThe great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.64,1:32:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In all the ones that I studied, it used to be in college,\Nyou studied the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.64,1:32:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a liberal education.\NNowadays, they avoid anything that's in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.64,1:32:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They stick to 190 or something.\NYeah, relativism coverage is about 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.08,1:32:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, where were we on the chart?\NOh, there they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.08,1:32:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NSo, there's all...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.12,1:32:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all the friends of my childhood.\NThey were my friends, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.12,1:32:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because that was a small ectomorph,\Nand the coach wouldn't allow me on the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.12,1:32:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, your bones are going to get all broken.\NThe doctor wouldn't give an okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.12,1:32:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I read, you know.\NSo, I was skinny with thick glasses
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.12,1:32:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and sat in a big chair and read books.\NSo, these are all my pals from childhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.12,1:33:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I get back on the other side,\NI'm looking forward to hanging out with them again.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.12,1:33:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates and Plato and all the folks.\NSo, anyway, these are the great books of the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.50,1:33:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristophanes, Aristotle, 498.\NAugustine, Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.53,1:33:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius.\NThat's what I'm reading as a child,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.53,1:33:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius.\NBut then normal childhood, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.53,1:33:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I kind of think of it, yeah.\NDescartes, of course, is brilliant
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.60,1:33:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because he pointed out the difference\Nbetween res interna and res externa.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.60,1:33:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The world as you see it\Nas compared to the world as you see it,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.82,1:33:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the world the way it is.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.92,1:33:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,To go beyond appearance, which is illusion,\Nto reality, which is essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.14,1:33:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And until we had consciousness calibration,\Nthere was frankly no way to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.14,1:33:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no way you could tell the essence of a thing.\NAll you had was the appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.14,1:33:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Descartes.\NWhat was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.48,1:34:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what I put this up for.\NThese are, and Hegel's, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.48,1:34:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Absolute,\Nwhich the relatives,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.55,1:34:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,both of us have warned you about,\Nis 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.74,1:34:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein was 499.\NFreud, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.74,1:34:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung was at 520.\NOkay, so this is the world Newtonian physics.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.96,1:34:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Plato at 485.\NAnd you see all the great minds of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.00,1:34:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The great minds of history.\NNow the last book,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.00,1:34:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the last book was on Freud.\NThe last book,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.00,1:34:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these were collected by\Nthe University of Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.00,1:34:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's only two things that stand out.\NKarl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.00,1:34:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See, they're all about 440, 460.\NKarl Marx doesn't belong in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.00,1:34:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He's only, well, he's at 130.\NEngels just makes it at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.06,1:34:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's on Marx's coattails.\NBut all this you can see is wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.06,1:35:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,has been wrong with,\Nrelativism really is a variation of Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.06,1:35:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So to drop from 450 to 130,\Nif you establish Marxism as a,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.06,1:35:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as a cultural reality,\Nyou end up as Mayo did in China
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.06,1:35:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with 30 million people starving to death.\N30 million people starving to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.06,1:35:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In North Korea,\Ntens of millions starve to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.06,1:35:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So Marxism hasn't worked out.\NIt leads to the masses starving to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.96,1:35:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was important politically.\NThat's why he's put in
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.96,1:35:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the great books of the Western world.\NSo we'll go back to the slides
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.96,1:35:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of what we were doing.\NHere you see reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.88,1:35:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a reasonable person,\Nreasonable person,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.88,1:35:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,has an 80% chance.\NLove at 500,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.88,1:35:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,only 89% are happy.\NI don't know what's the matter with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.88,1:35:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What more than love do you want?\NI don't know what's the matter with those people.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.88,1:35:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to examine some of these people,\Nholdbacks here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.88,1:35:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're peculiar.\NMaybe they're not all there or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.88,1:35:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NAt 540,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.92,1:36:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,love becomes unconditional.\NThe 12-step groups calibrate at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.92,1:36:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,540.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.92,1:36:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the great ways to God\Nis through the 12-step programs,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.11,1:36:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,\Nthe miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.11,1:36:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,other things,\Nother than,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.11,1:36:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because not everybody finds religion,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.11,1:36:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,acceptable.\NSo they say,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.11,1:36:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\Nhow can I,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.11,1:36:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Ntranscend and get somewhere
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.11,1:36:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,without going to church\Nand being a religionist?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.11,1:36:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The 12-step groups.\NUnconditional love means
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.11,1:36:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving people\Nno matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.11,1:36:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't forgive them\Nif you don't love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.11,1:36:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive them\Nif you don't love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.11,1:36:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive them\Nif you don't love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.11,1:36:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive them\Nif you don't love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.17,1:36:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive them\Nno matter what
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.17,1:36:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you accept\NSocrates'
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.17,1:36:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding\Nthat all people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.17,1:36:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,only choose\Nwhat they concern
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.17,1:36:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the good.\NSo now you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.17,1:36:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easy to forgive them\Nbecause what is ignorance?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.17,1:36:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignorance is just not knowing,\Nknowing essence
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.17,1:36:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from appearance\Nfor which we forgive people.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.17,1:36:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we forgive them?\NBecause we see
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.17,1:36:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from the evolution\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.17,1:36:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that many people\Nhave not evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.17,1:36:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to the capacity\Nwhere they could see
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.17,1:37:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of a thing.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.17,1:37:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you forgive them\Nbecause you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.17,1:37:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they haven't evolved\Nto that point yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.17,1:37:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For the same reason\Nwe don't hate a kid
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.17,1:37:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with a low IQ\Nbecause he doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.17,1:37:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,get straight A's.\NSo love becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.56,1:37:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional\Nat 540,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.56,1:37:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at 570,\Nat sainthood.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.56,1:37:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,570,\Nall the saints
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.56,1:37:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate at 570.\NAs I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.91,1:37:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the current pope\Nis practically
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.91,1:37:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,at 570\Nand the Buddhist fellow,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.91,1:37:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever his name is,\NI forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.28,1:37:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\NI understand him
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.70,1:37:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because he laughs\Nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.70,1:37:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dalai Lama.\NThe Dalai Lama,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.70,1:37:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah.\NThere's somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.70,1:37:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was talking to,\Nsome famous person
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.70,1:37:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,on the phone\Nand I was laughing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.70,1:37:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time\Nand she was annoyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.73,1:37:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nshe doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.73,1:37:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,why I'm laughing\Nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.86,1:37:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,\Nwell,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.86,1:37:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the same reason\Nthe Dalai Lama
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.86,1:37:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,laughs all the time\Nbecause life
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.86,1:37:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is a constant\Nhysterical comedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.95,1:38:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even as the\Nheadsman's coming over,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.95,1:38:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a comedy\Nbecause you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.95,1:38:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole thing\Nis an absurd drama.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.95,1:38:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You're laughing\Nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.40,1:38:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,\Npeace is at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.40,1:38:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,\Nthis is the peace
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.43,1:38:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of God.\N600 is the
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.43,1:38:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,peace of God\Nand 600
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.43,1:38:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is the beginning\Nof the levels
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.43,1:38:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of enlightenment.\NAt 600,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.43,1:38:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't really\Nfunction.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.43,1:38:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really\Ndo anything
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.65,1:38:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,at 600\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.65,1:38:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's non-linear,\Nit's eternal,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.65,1:38:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it's forever\Nand from 600
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.13,1:38:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on up,\Nyou can leave
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.13,1:38:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the world\Nanytime you like
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.13,1:38:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's invitational.\NAt 600,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.13,1:38:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize\Nthat you
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.32,1:38:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are not\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.03,1:38:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the state\Nof bliss
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.03,1:38:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nblissful.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.82,1:38:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not necessary\Nto continue on.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.82,1:38:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nand if these states
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.98,1:38:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,hit you,\Nyou can get
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.98,1:38:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,an okay\Nto leave
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.98,1:39:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,at any time.\NIf you're driving
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.98,1:39:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,down the highway,\Nit's sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.98,1:39:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what to do about it.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.98,1:39:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\Nshould I pull over
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.59,1:39:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or not pull over?\NI guess I better pull over.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.59,1:39:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to enjoy\Nthe light of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.58,1:39:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NAnd there are
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.58,1:39:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,very few people\Nat those higher levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.58,1:39:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is\Nfor,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.64,1:39:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at 600\Nyou can leave
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.64,1:39:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and\N50%
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.64,1:39:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that are\Nat level 600
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.84,1:39:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,will leave.\NYou have the option
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.54,1:39:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave.\NEach level,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.54,1:39:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as you advance,\Nagain,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.54,1:39:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a 50%\Nchance to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.54,1:39:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At 850,\Nyou have it,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.54,1:39:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you can leave,\Nyou can leave
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.67,1:39:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally,\Nthere's hardly anyone
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.67,1:39:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,left on the planet\NNot because it's a rare, but because everyone leaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.71,1:40:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to tell you, but everybody, you realize you don't have to continue on.\NSome people, by virtue of some prior commitment and agreement, return to the world and function again.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.83,1:40:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually as teachers, and that's their agreement.\NThe karmic fulfillment of that potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.43,1:40:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To share what you have become with others.\NAnd by sharing that, what you have become with others, they become their own potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.30,1:40:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's to facilitate other people becoming their own potential.\NIt's the reason to choose to continue on.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.94,1:40:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that makes it all worth it.\NOh, Lord, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.04,1:40:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, spiritual practice and daily life.\NPeople say, how can I get more involved?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.31,1:40:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodwill towards all.\NAll of life, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.15,1:40:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget, when the headsman comes to you, worry about how he's feeling.\NDon't feel guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.97,1:40:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NYou're doing your job.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.09,1:40:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.\NAnd tip him.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.55,1:41:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I always tip the headsman.\NGoodwill towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.65,1:41:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.44,1:41:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual practice and daily life.\NYou don't have to isolate yourself or discontinue.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.22,1:41:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't compartmentalize your life.\NBecome your own spiritual practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.22,1:41:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when I give sermons someplace, I always say, you know, become the prayer.\NBecome that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.62,1:41:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't practice that.\NDon't think that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.78,1:41:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't memorize that.\NBe that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.68,1:41:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Be that.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.60,1:41:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Be that.\NSo the practice is education.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.54,1:41:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And the choice of teachers.\NCalibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.27,1:41:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Always calibrate the teachers and calibrate the pathway.\NIn your daily routine, you include contemplation as a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.11,1:42:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I say turn your life into a prayer,\Nyou become that which is supportive of all of life and can see what the limitations of life are.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.27,1:42:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you tend to uplift life by virtue of that which you have become.\NAnd meditation and contemplation become part of your life as does prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.46,1:42:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation to me is a way of being in the world.\NYou see, meditation has its place.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.12,1:42:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But, and I spent many years meditating, but meditation tends to take you out of the world.\NYou can't function in today's world and spend all your time meditating.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.98,1:42:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it when I came out to wherever we are here.\NAnd it didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.78,1:42:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I just stayed in that beatific state, you know, for, you know, just stayed there.\NBut you can't function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.84,1:42:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So being contemplative then is, I compare it to sort\Nof Yin position.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.02,1:43:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplative means, you see, Yang is very this.\NGod, I got to have this, and I'm going to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.20,1:43:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very Yang.\NA contemplative way of being in the world is a Yin posture.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.58,1:43:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychically you have become that which is open.\NAnd by virtue of that which is open, your Yin side of you summons forth
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.48,1:43:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you need.\NYou go to bed with a question on your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.87,1:43:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wake up and the answer is there.\NNot through any doingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.24,1:43:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of that which you become,\Nyour life becomes a supplication.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.88,1:43:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To thee, O Lord, do I surrender my will in the matter.\NAnd you ask that the Lord reveal to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.34,1:44:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're asking so life becomes a continuous revelation\Nwhich eventually becomes the continuous miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.09,1:44:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.80,1:44:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So prayer then.\NDedication.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.74,1:44:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing you begin to notice\Nis the incredible beauty and perfection of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.76,1:44:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At first this sort of knocks you out\Nand it's very difficult to function.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.26,1:44:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere you go, the beauty is overwhelming.\NI can remember being in an airport
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.40,1:44:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a couple of millions looked at each other\Nand I,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.33,1:44:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the glance, you could see the love.\NThe presence of the love just knocked me out.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.53,1:44:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how I got onto the plane.\NI was just, it was just,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.27,1:44:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you're just blissed out by the incredible beauty\Nof all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.09,1:44:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As you walk through nature, you'll see the perfection.\NWhen you see the incredible beauty of weeds,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.88,1:44:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,they stop being weeds.\NWhen you walk by a weed and you look at it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.12,1:44:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see its incredible perfection,\Nthere it stands there like the most magnificent sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.72,1:45:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see everything is like a magnificent sculpture.\NEvery weed stands there displaying its incredible perfection and beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.62,1:45:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you become conscious and you're witness\Nto the incredible perfection and beauty of all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.53,1:45:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because creation is God manifest, the Godhead through creation.\NSo you see that creation is ongoing and forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.13,1:45:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no linear God with a beginning and an ending.\NAnd the beginning was so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.51,1:45:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a way of writing it up.\NThat which has no beginning has no ending.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.12,1:45:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it has no cause.\NSo you live in a universe which is beyond causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.65,1:45:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that everything is unfolding.\NIts potentiality is actualizing by virtue of the infinite power of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.65,1:46:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the ultimate context.\NThe infinite power of divinity is an all-encompassing field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.25,1:46:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which potentiality arises into actuality through emergence.\NThrough emergence.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.37,1:46:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the potentiality of the human spirit,\Nthe eventuality of it is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.82,1:46:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about spiritual evolution.\NIt's inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.77,1:46:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to work hard to avoid it.\NBecause the potentiality is within you and therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.97,1:46:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in the infinite presence of divinity,\Nwhich is the source of all existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.17,1:46:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you can become,\Nthat potentiality begins to manifest as an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.55,1:46:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you watch the focus on the beauty of all things\Nand you note the perfection of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.54,1:47:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch the unfoldment.\NSo there's no longer causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.84,1:47:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the unfoldment.\NThe willingness to surrender all these negativities.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.50,1:47:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to accept God's will.\NThe choices, situations, the ego and its problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.66,1:47:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, instead of being mad at the ego.\NSo now we have a new way of seeing the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.06,1:47:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is the leftover of the evolution of the protoplasm as the mammalian species.\NIt was necessary for survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.72,1:47:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was what you owe your survival to.\NWithout the ego, you wouldn't be here to complain about your ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.72,1:47:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, thank you, ego, for getting me to the point that I can transcend, you know.\NGet off the bus,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.12,1:47:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and get on a different kind of a vehicle.\NBut without the bus, you wouldn't get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.02,1:47:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So God's willing to accept all these assets, the ego and its problems.\NSo instead of making the ego your enemy,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.10,1:47:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you own it as though it's a pet.\NIt's your little pet, left over from prehistoric times.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.86,1:48:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you hate other people.\NOf course, you want to be dominant.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.66,1:48:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you want to be greedy and eat it all up.\NOf course, you want to copulate around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.58,1:48:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know.\NIs that your animal side?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.00,1:48:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You eventually accept God's infinite love and mercy.\NAnd, all right, we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.10,1:48:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget which is the last chart.\NGot to watch the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.16,1:48:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How much more time we got?\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.25,1:48:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.06,1:48:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOh, these are practices to move you ahead in your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.26,1:48:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The more, the farther ahead you are in your level of consciousness, the more of what you hold in mind tends to materialize.\NYou have to be careful what you hold in mind because it's there, right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.46,1:48:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, choose holy company.\NThat's why, you know, avoid that which is obviously dedicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.70,1:48:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause of their energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.20,1:49:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really just because of their energy.\NYeah, practice Socrates' view.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.89,1:49:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,See others as being programmed.\NThey can't help being what they are because they've been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.19,1:49:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the media program.\NEverybody all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.59,1:49:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to give you the statistics on it.\NI'm working on a book called Spiritual Reality in Modern Man.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.59,1:49:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's depressing.\NI wish I'd never started that book.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.07,1:49:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I think when I knew less, I was happier.\NI mean, you calibrate the most, you know, popular shows on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.99,1:49:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You finally calibrate 160.\N160.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.99,1:49:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissism, cruelty, sexuality, seduction, 160.\NSee others as programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.03,1:50:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You make a commitment, visualize your goal of loving this towards all of life and being grateful for what you have and be satisfied with where you're at.\NNow, your mind tends to, the more often you choose a certain thing, the more likely you're going to choose that again.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.38,1:50:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called quantum Zeno effect.\NThe quantum Zeno effect is out of randomness.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.00,1:50:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The more often you choose this, the more often you choose that.\NAlthough the next time is potentially random, the more likely you will choose this, the more likely.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.20,1:50:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called the tension set.\NSo by declaration of spiritual intention and choosing constantly the good as you come to understand it, the likelihood is that you will choose it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.82,1:50:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So free will, of which there's all kinds of sophomoric argumentation, is a dominance of likelihoods, the attractor field that you have assigned to.\NThere's a greater.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.92,1:50:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Greater.\NLikelihood that you will choose to forgive the person.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.72,1:51:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you're angry and see them as wrong, you won't be satisfied with that.\NYou say, you know, he's a SOB.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.22,1:51:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He deserves what he gets.\NThen in the bed, you think, but yeah, but the next day you so you meditate on it and you play with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.48,1:51:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're not satisfied that you hate the guy or you fear the person, et cetera.\NYou're not satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.08,1:51:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because you have spiritual goals and you say, so you ask for a miracle.\NYou say, dear Lord, I'd like to see this differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.38,1:51:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe nothing will happen at all.\NNelson, you're driving down the highway a month later and all of a sudden you got a totally different way of seeing it out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.34,1:51:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can see now differently.\NWhat else could he do?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.84,1:51:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What else could he do?\NAll he could do is hate you and kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.64,1:51:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what else could he do?\NAnd then you forgive people for killing you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.04,1:51:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how the times you've been killed.\NYou don't remember all those lifetimes, but even killed a lot, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.64,1:51:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't kill.\NKilled is one of the ways we usually ended it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.54,1:52:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We got killed.\NYou end up with benevolence and mindfulness means paying attention to that mindset.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.88,1:52:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're willing to surrender narcissism, the wonderful me.\NYou see how spiritual growth is not concordant with the current media world of you as the wonderful me.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.97,1:52:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Time Magazine had one.\NI thought Time Magazine cover was brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.97,1:52:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a stroke of genius, the mirror on the front of Time Magazine.\NThe ultimate, we are the ultimate of the narcissistic, me, self-indulgent.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.19,1:52:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it around the clock.\NMe, wonderful me.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.66,1:52:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And my spot, my, you know, the blogs are now 90% of blogs are fallacious, you know, 90%.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.22,1:53:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So willing to surrender all the adrenaline.\NThe victimhood, the hurt feelings, look at the injustice collectors, willing to stop needing to win, and most importantly, to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.74,1:53:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to be right is one of the addictions that is very hard to get off.\NTo be right is so important, we're willing to die for it, and we're willing to kill you if you think you're right.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.03,1:53:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think you're right, you've just bought yourself a death sentence.\NIt's so important.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.63,1:53:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more important to be right.\NAnd, of course, you watch the evening news channel, whatever they are, and you get over seeing yourself as the causal, primary causal agent.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.02,1:53:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You see yourself as only a part of a process in which your potentiality is actualizing because of the agreement of your own will.\NIf you decided against it with your will, then you've just shut off those options, but you've also shut off the karmic benefit of those options.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.41,1:54:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness of self and others.\NSelfless service, those are the great yogas, and, oh, I didn't tell you how to get off the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.91,1:54:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do that before we quit.\NI know, we've got just time to kill the mind while we're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.14,1:54:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is your biggest aggravation, and the classic spiritual writings are that enlightenment is between two thoughts.\NThat's a mistranslation of the Buddha, he never said such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.06,1:54:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the people who listen to him, that's as far as they got it.\NIt was a ballpark.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.28,1:54:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the infinite is prior to thoughts.\NIt's below thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.90,1:54:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot get between two thoughts.\NThoughts occur in one-tenth-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:48.60,1:54:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time you notice, by the time your perceiver perceives that, that one-tenth-thousandth is already gone.\NThe minute you begin to notice it, it's over already.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:57.10,1:55:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot catch your own tail.\NThat's why enlightenment is very rare.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:01.60,1:55:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You practically never have it.\NNever, never.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.60,1:55:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In a whole century, maybe, one or two.\NIf you're looking for enlightenment between two thoughts, you'll never find it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:10.52,1:55:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThe enlightenment is the nothingness, the potentiality, which is underneath your thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.52,1:55:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind is actually still and silent.\NNinety-nine percent of your mind is still and silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.52,1:55:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,One percent is busy thinking and talking.\NAnd you pay attention to the one percent and think that's your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.52,1:55:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you right now where to find it.\NGo away.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.52,1:55:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's right now.\NThere is an infinite field of silence below your thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.55,1:55:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not prior.\NIt's not between.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:39.55,1:55:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's underneath your thoughts.\NAll the thinkingness and mentalization is coming out of an infinite, silent field.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.55,1:55:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the thought of a little dogginess sort of grabs on.\NThen it becomes Rover.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.55,1:56:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it becomes the story about a Rover got run over and oh, we all cried and married him and all.\NSad.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.99,1:56:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Underneath everybody's thinkingness right now, there's an infinite silence below all the thinkingness of everybody here.\NThere is nothing going on at all underneath the minds of everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.84,1:56:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.84,1:56:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NYour mind is not thinking anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:26.58,1:56:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an infinite, silent potentiality.\NYour mind right now is not thinking anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.70,1:56:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a hearingness of this voice and its talkingness.\NThe only reason you can hear that is because your mind is actually silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.76,1:56:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Underneath the hearing of all this talkingness that's going on is an infinite, profound silence with no beginning and no end.\NForever.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.40,1:57:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,An infinite potentiality.\NEverybody willing to give up thinking for two seconds?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.47,1:57:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all quit thinking, okay?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:04.60,1:57:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don't try to stop thinking.\NIf you try to stop thinking, you'll have to stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.82,1:57:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stop thinking, you'll be stuck with trying to stop thinking.\NYou can't stop thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.52,1:57:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNow, we're going to dive below, like into the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.37,1:57:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite silence.\NThat's where it is, what you're looking for, is the infinite silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.00,1:57:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the infinite silence, potentiality is actualizing into actuality, and that's what we call life.\NThat's what we call who I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.00,1:57:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we call what the world is.\NBut you can see that's all just a presentation with no innate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.00,1:57:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're all free forever.\NThank you, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.00,1:58:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And thank you.\NGod bless you all.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:29.92,1:58:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been my joy.
